# Bounceable Tappable Components

Every tappable element in the app must produce a spring scale bounce on press. Never use a bare `Pressable` without bounce feedback.

## Standard case

Use `RNBounceable` from `@freakycoder/react-native-bounceable` as a wrapper around any tappable content:

```tsx
import RNBounceable from '@freakycoder/react-native-bounceable';

<RNBounceable onPress={handlePress}>
  <View className="bg-primary rounded-2xl py-4 items-center justify-center">
    <Text>Tap me</Text>
  </View>
</RNBounceable>
```

Put visual styling (background, border radius, padding) on an inner `View` child — `RNBounceable` handles sizing and press behaviour.

## Link asChild case

When `Link asChild` (expo-router) needs to inject navigation into the tappable element, use `RNBounceable` as the direct child of `Link`:

```tsx
import RNBounceable from '@freakycoder/react-native-bounceable';

<Link href="/somewhere" asChild>
  <RNBounceable>
    <Link.AppleZoom>
      {/* content */}
    </Link.AppleZoom>
  </RNBounceable>
</Link>
```

## Rules

- Never use a bare `Pressable` — always use `RNBounceable`
- Never use `TouchableOpacity` or `TouchableHighlight` — use `RNBounceable` instead
- Import: `import RNBounceable from '@freakycoder/react-native-bounceable'`
